### English Title:
Houthi Forces Vow to Continue Military Operations Against Israel and U.S. Forces

### English Text Summary:
The Houthi movement has pledged to continue its military operations against Israel and U.S. forces in the region following deadly U.S. airstrikes in western Yemen that killed dozens. In a statement, the Yemeni armed forces controlled by the Houthis declared their commitment to support the Palestinian people until Israeli aggression in Gaza ceases and the blockade is lifted. The group claimed to have conducted a military operation targeting a military site near Ben Gurion Airport in Israel and asserted that they also targeted U.S. aircraft carriers and warships in the Red Sea and Arabian Sea. The U.S. airstrikes on Thursday resulted in significant casualties, marking one of the deadliest days in the recent escalation of U.S. military action against the Iran-backed group.

